examples.korean: I bet she was annoyed at having to write it out again. 발음듣기 그것을 완전히 다시 써야 했으니 그녀가 틀림없이 짜증이 났을 거야. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I bet she was annoyed at having to write it out again. 발음

examples.korean: We can fix the ship’s exact position at the time the fire broke out. 발음듣기 불이 났을 때 그 배가 있었던 정확한 위치를 우리가 알아낼 수 있어요. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: We can fix the ship’s exact position at the time the fire broke out. 발음

examples.korean: You have to make hay while the sun shines. 발음듣기 볕이 났을 때 풀을 말려라(좋은 기회를 놓치지 마라). DARAKWON
examples.english: You have to make hay while the sun shines. 발음

examples.korean: Never do anything when you are in a temper, for you will do everything wrong. (Baltasar Gracian) 발음듣기 화 났을 때는 아무 일도 하지 말라. 하는 일마다 잘 못 될 것이다. (발타사르 그라시안, 자기관리명언) 명언/속담
examples.english: Never do anything when you are in a temper, for you will do everything wrong. (Baltasar Gracian) 발음

examples.korean: Lots of people want to ride with you in the limo, but what you want is someone who will take the bus with you when the limo breaks down. (Oprah Winfrey) 발음듣기 여러분과 리무진을 타고 싶어하는 사람은 많겠지만, 정작 여러분이 원하는 사람은 리무진이 고장났을 때 같이 버스를 타 줄 사람입니다. (오프라 윈프리, 친구명언) 명언/속담
examples.english: Lots of people want to ride with you in the limo, but what you want is someone who will take the bus with you when the limo breaks down. (Oprah Winfrey) 발음
